<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05036f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05036f">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05036f"> 36(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> amphibalus</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Martin rose from his prayers, and stripping himself beneath the sheltering folds of his <mark>amphibalus</mark> (a large cloak that monks wore over their habit on public occasions), he handled his under tunic to the man and sent him away. <small> Margaret Maitland, <a name="MMLL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#MMLL"><cite title="source">Life and Legends of St. Martin of Tours (316-397)</cite></a> (1908) 91</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
